 A commonly used pattern based on ~ r19.29 , version with two restricted quantifiers. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 26-Nov-2017.)
statement:
r19.29vva.1 $e |- ( ( ( ( ph /\ x e. A ) /\ y e. B ) /\ ps ) -> ch ) $.
r19.29vva.2 $e |- ( ph -> E. x e. A E. y e. B ps ) $.
r19.29vva $p |- ( ph -> ch ) $.
$d A y $.
$d ch x y $.
$d ph x y $.
